         Im very excited about these pet changes, rather, im very excited about the pet/xp change, although im still unclear as to how DC pets will effect solo/group xp</P><P>my concerns wtih the 1st 2 points:</P><P>pets not breaking mez,<BR>definaetly the good outweighs the bad here, but what if you WANT your pet to break mez?, its no longer possible for it to do so, but again, not that big a deal considering how good this is other than that</P><P>indifferent pets, <BR>from my experience, rarely does a pet go off and bring mobs back<BR>this change will alliviate(sp) these sort of problems(or pets causing aggro just via low lvl proximity), but with some pathing as it stands, if your pet is on a mobs hate list, and your pet runs off(via pathing), is the hate list attatched to your pet or through assist range off the mob being killed?</P><P>if its the latter, thats excellet, if its the former, then its a nice change, but not as impactful as it woudl appear to be on its surface</P><P><BR>all in all, very good changes</P><P>its kind of funny, im memming lvl55 haste nowadays wiht my spec pet, and with my silverflank belt, i almost feel like..... a pet class!</P><P></P><P>Kriista Silence<BR>Warlock of Veeshan</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=103458" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=103458</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
