         Rich,</P><P>Thank you for this great news! It looks like you and the Dev Team have given pets and pet classes some serious consideration and it shows. These changes are most welcome and a good portent for the future viability of pet classes--mages, necros, beastlords, enchanters and others.</P><P>The new pet experience rules make perfect sense. This is cause for celebration. No longer do we have to compete with pets for experience!</P><P>Pets classes have been seriously penalized on raids because of the danger of bad pathing--the pet agroing the whole zone and of course pets breaking mez. Pets will no longer be a liablity to a guild. Instead they will be an assest. Cheers!</P><P>The only outstanding issues are:</P><P>-improving basic resists of pets so they will last more than 30 secs from mob AE</P><P>-improving ATK, HPS and AC of pets perhaps this can be added to the current pet buff/haste spells ie. Intensify Death, Augment Death, etc.</P><P>Rich, thanks for being one of the first SOE designers to publicly come out and establish a dialogue with the players. You're proven to us that you really have listened to the concerns of the pet class community. These changes are monumental. I hope you continue to look at caster balancing with the same kind of attention to detail and professionalism that you have demonstrated here. All I can say is thank you!!!</P><P>One happy necro!</P><P></P><P>Dornette<BR>60 necromancer<BR>The Nameless<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
